    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 28,
        "summary": "The wicked flee when no man pursues\u2014Whoever walks uprightly will be saved\u2014A faithful man will abound with blessings.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The wicked flee when no man pursueth: but the righteous are bold as a lion.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 26:17; Amos 9:1.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:40.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the transgression of a land many are the princes thereof: but by a man of understanding and knowledge the state thereof shall be prolonged.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A poor man that oppresseth the poor is like a sweeping rain which leaveth no food.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Oppression.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They that forsake the law praise the wicked: but such as keep the law contend with them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Evil men understand not judgment: but they that seek the Lord understand all things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 88:67.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Better is the poor that walketh in his uprightness, than he that is perverse in his ways, though he be rich.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:9; 19:1.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso keepeth the law is a wise son: but he that is a companion of riotous men shameth his father.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0gluttonous. Luke 15:13 (12\u201313). TG\u00a0Rioting and Reveling.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that by usury and unjust gain increaseth his substance, he shall gather it for him that will pity the poor.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Usury.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 11:20.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that turneth away his ear from hearing the law, even his prayer shall be abomination.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 29:18; D&C 88:35 (34\u201335).",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 109:7; Moro. 7:6 (6\u20137).",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso causeth the righteous to go astray in an evil way, he shall fall himself into his own pit: but the upright shall have good things in possession.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Justice.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 26:27; 1\u00a0Ne. 22:14.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The rich man is wise in his own conceit; but the poor that hath understanding searcheth him out.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 32:12 (12\u201313); D&C 104:16.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When righteous men do rejoice, there is great glory: but when the wicked rise, a man is hidden.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 11:10.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that covereth his sins shall not prosper: but whoso confesseth and forsaketh them shall have mercy.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 31:33; Luke 12:2 (1\u20133); 1\u00a0Jn. 1:10; D&C 1:3; 121:37 (36\u201338).",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Confession.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Repent.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Happy is the man that feareth alway: but he that hardeneth his heart shall fall into mischief.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hardheartedness.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As a roaring lion, and a ranging bear; so is a wicked ruler over the poor people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 22:25.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The prince that wanteth understanding is also a great oppressor: but he that hateth covetousness shall prolong his days.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covet.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A man that doeth violence to the blood of any person shall flee to the pit; let no man stay him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 1:13 (13\u201314).",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0flee to the sepulchre (grave); i.e., flee to death.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso walketh uprightly shall be saved: but he that is perverse in his ways shall fall at once.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that tilleth his land shall have plenty of bread: but he that followeth after vain persons shall have poverty enough.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A faithful man shall abound with blessings: but he that maketh haste to be rich shall not be innocent.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haste.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To have respect of persons is not good: for for a piece of bread that man will transgress.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:23; James 2:9.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 13:19.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bread.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that hasteth to be rich hath an evil eye, and considereth not that poverty shall come upon him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that rebuketh a man afterwards shall find more favour than he that flattereth with the tongue.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 27:5.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Flatter.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso robbeth his father or his mother, and saith, It is no transgression; the same is the companion of a destroyer.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is of a proud heart stirreth up strife: but he that putteth his trust in the Lord shall be made fat.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 13:10; 2\u00a0Ne. 28:12 (12\u201313).",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strife.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 11:12; 84:116.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0prosperous.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that trusteth in his own heart is a fool: but whoso walketh wisely, he shall be delivered.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust Not in the Arm of Flesh.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that giveth unto the poor shall not lack: but he that hideth his eyes shall have many a curse.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Almsgiving; Poor; Welfare.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When the wicked rise, men hide themselves: but when they perish, the righteous increase.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 98:9.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}